---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon";
import Button from "../../../Button/button.astro";
import TextSection from "../../../textSection/TextSection.astro";
import ProductsContainer from "../../products/productsContainer/productsContainer.astro";
import ProductCard from "../../products/productCard/productCard.astro";

import BestMotivationalBooks from "./BestMotivationalBooks.astro";
import BestMotivationalBooksAthletes from "./BestMotivationalBooksAthletes.astro";

import ArticleFaqs from "./ArticleFaqs.astro";
import ListOfContent from "./ListOfContent.astro";
---

<article class="pt-3 px-[20px] sm:p-0 max-w-3xl mx-auto sm:w-11/12 sm:mx-auto">
  <!-- List of content -->
  <ListOfContent />

  <!-- <Body /> -->
  <BestMotivationalBooks />
  <BestMotivationalBooksAthletes />

  <!-- Conclusion -->

  <TextSection>
    <h3 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h3>
    <p>
      The books mentioned in this article are all inspiring and motivational.
      There is something for everyone, no matter the situation or goal they are
      trying to achieve. From biographical tales of perseverence to strategies
      on unlocking your full potential, each have the power to help you take a
      step forward and achieve your goals. One book we would like to leave you
      with is <a class="underline link--theme" href="#"
        >The Subtle Art of Not Giving a F*ck</a
      > by Mark Manson. It's a great choice for those who don't want anything too
      heavy or 'gimmicky' and provides practical advice for finding freedom from
      our relentless desire to be awesome at everything we do! So what are you waiting
      for? Get out there, buy the book, and start taking charge of your life today!
    </p>
  </TextSection>

  <!-- Info -->

  <TextSection>
    <h2 id="why-economics-books-matter" class="text-base sm:text-lg pt-6">
      Wich is the best book for athletes?
    </h2>
    <p class="">
      As an athlete, you know that the mental game can be just as important as
      the physical.
    </p>
    <p class="">
      So, which book should you pick up to give you the mental edge you need to
      push through those tough workouts or competition days?.
    </p>
    <p class="">
      From autobiographies of legends like Michael Jordan and Serena Williams to
      more instructional reads like "The Mind Gym" by Gary Mack and David
      Casstevens, there is no shortage of options.
    </p>

    <div class="flex justify-center items-center pb-6">
      <Button href="#best-books-for-athletes" customIcon>
        Best Books For Athletes
        <Fragment slot="icon">
          <Icon name="ic:baseline-chevron-right" />
        </Fragment>
      </Button>
    </div>

    <p class="">
      If you don't know how to decide my recomendation is "Peak Performance"
    </p>

    <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
      <ProductCard products={1} />
    </div>
  </TextSection>

  <ArticleFaqs />
</article>
